Quiz 2
Try all three questions on the quiz; the third is on the back of this page. You have 15 minutes in
total. Make sure you give yourself time for each part. Good luck!
1. "The use of a good conceptual model is [...] fundamental to good design" Don Norman
(a) What does Don Norman mean by a conceptual model?
2. The Unix copy command
W1 2009
(b) Give one concrete example of a conceptual model provided by the Google Maps graphical
user interface.
cp file1 file2
copies the contents of filel into file2, creating file2 if it does not already exist.
However, when this command is used with filel as "CPSC 101.txt" and file2 as "notes.txt",
the error message
cp: notes.txt not found
is returned. Why does the command fail?
3. Look at the Scratch script below and answer the following questions.
(a) What is the position of the sprite after the instruction labeled 1?
(b) How many times is the instruction labeled 2 executed?
(c) What is the position of the sprite at the end of the second iteration of the repeat loop?
(d) As best you can, describe in your own words what the sprite does when the script is
executed.
set counter to -100
go to x: 0 y: counter
repeat 4
change counter by 30
glide 0.5 secs to x: -25 y: counter
change counter by 30
glide 0.5 secs to x: 25 y: counter
1
2
